9 COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to H.P. 549, L.D. 863, “An Act to Exempt
10 Internet Raffles Conducted by Certain Organizations with Prizes of $2,500 or Less from
11 Registration and Licensing Requirements”
12 Amend the bill by striking out the title and substituting the following:
13 'An Act to Allow a Person or Organization Conducting a Raffle to Use an Approved
14 Payment Management System'
15 Amend the bill by striking out everything after the enacting clause and inserting the
16 following:
17 'Sec. 1. 17 MRSA §1837-C, as enacted by PL 2021, c. 636, §3, is amended to read:
18 §1837-C. Raffle entry by payment management system
19 1. Definitions. As used in this section, unless the context indicates otherwise, the
20 following terms have the following meanings.
21 A. "Geolocation technology" means a computer program or data collection system that
22 can be used to identify the geographic location of a person an individual interacting
23 with that computer program or data collection system through the Internet.
24 B. "Payment management system" means a mobile application or other digital
25 platform and the accompanying computer software used to accept payment for a raffle
26 chance or ticket through the Internet.
27 2. Use of payment management system. When conducting a raffle under section
28 1837‑A that is not an Internet raffle, an eligible a person or organization may accept
29 payment for a raffle chance or ticket from a payment management system if:
30 A. The payment management system is approved by the director under subsection 3;
31 B. The raffle chance or ticket is purchased by a person an individual who is at least 18
32 years of age; and
Page 1 - 132LR1444(02)
COMMITTEE AMENDMENT

COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to H.P. 549, L.D. 863
1 C. The raffle chance or ticket is purchased by a person an individual who is physically
2 located in the State or another state where the purchase of that raffle chance or ticket
3 would be legal under the laws of that state.
4 If the eligible person or organization determines that the purchase of a raffle chance or
5 ticket is made in violation of paragraph B or C, the person or organization shall immediately
6 refund the payment and void the raffle chance or ticket associated with the purchase.
7 If the eligible person or organization conducts a raffle in which a winner receives a firearm,
8 the transfer of that firearm to the winner must be processed through a holder of a federal
9 license for a dealer in firearms who is not a dealer in destructive devices under 18 United
10 States Code, Section 923(a)(3)(B).
11 An eligible A person or organization that fails to comply with this subsection commits a
12 civil violation punishable by a fine of not less than $500 and not more than $5,000.
13 3. Approval of payment management system. Upon request from an eligible a
14 person or organization, the director may approve a payment management system for use
15 by the person or organization in conducting a raffle that is not an Internet raffle only if the
16 director determines that the payment management system:
17 A. Does not permit the extension of credit from the eligible person or organization to
18 a person an individual who purchases a raffle chance or ticket;
19 B. Does not permit a person an individual to initiate a transaction to purchase a raffle
20 chance or ticket and finalize the transaction by providing payment by mail;
21 C. Includes adequate measures to ensure that a person an individual who purchases a
22 raffle chance or ticket is at least 18 years of age;
23 D. Includes geolocation technology to determine with a reasonable degree of certainty
24 the state in which a person an individual who purchases a raffle chance or ticket is
25 physically located at the time the purchase is made and allows an eligible a person or
26 organization to prevent a person an individual from purchasing a raffle chance or ticket
27 while the person individual is physically located in a state where the purchase of that
28 raffle chance or ticket would not be legal under the laws of that state;
29 E. Provides for the immediate refund of any payment to purchase a raffle chance or
30 ticket made by a person an individual who the person or organization discovers is under
31 18 years of age at the time of purchase or was physically located in a state where the
32 raffle being conducted is not legally permitted at the time of purchase;
33 F. Includes adequate measures to protect the privacy and security of payment
34 information submitted by persons individuals who purchase raffle chances or tickets
35 during the purchase process; and
36 G. Enables the eligible person or organization to satisfy the record-keeping and
37 reporting requirements in subsection 6 as well as any other requirements established
38 by the Gambling Control Unit by rule.
39 4. Payment; eligible organization. A payment management system approved by the
40 director under this section may permit the use of a debit card or other payment method that
41 the an eligible organization as described in section 1832, subsection 2 uses to accept
42 membership dues from out-of-state members and may allow a member of the eligible
Page 2 - 132LR1444(02)
COMMITTEE AMENDMENT

COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to H.P. 549, L.D. 863
413 organization to request that payment for a raffle chance or ticket be made using the
424 member's funds already within the possession of the eligible organization.
3 5. Guidance for raffle operators. Upon receipt of a request to approve a payment
4 management system under subsection 3, the director shall provide the eligible person or
5 organization with a guidance document including any information the director determines
6 necessary to assist the eligible person or organization in complying with the requirements
7 of this section.
8 6. Record-keeping and reporting requirements. In addition to the record-keeping
9 requirements under section 1839, an eligible a person or organization that uses a payment
10 management system to conduct a raffle under section 1837-A for which a registration is
11 required shall:
12 A. Retain for a period of 3 years an electronic copy of each receipt for the sale of a
13 raffle chance or ticket sold using the payment management system;
14 B. Retain for a period of one year a physical copy of each raffle ticket stub generated
15 by the sale of a chance or ticket for a raffle sold using the payment management system;
16 C. Maintain raffle ticket stubs retained under paragraph A or B separately for each
17 individual raffle;
18 D. Provide receipts for raffle chances or tickets and raffle ticket stubs retained under
19 this subsection to the Gambling Control Unit on request; and
20 E. Submit an annual report to the Gambling Control Unit that includes the number of
21 raffles conducted using a payment management system during the year covered by the
22 report and the amount of gross receipts for each of those raffles.
23 An eligible A person or organization that fails to comply with this subsection commits a
24 civil violation punishable by a fine of not less than $500 and not more than $5,000.
25 Sec. 2. Appropriations and allocations. The following appropriations and
26 allocations are made.
27 PUBLIC SAFETY, DEPARTMENT OF
28 Gambling Control Board Z002
29 Initiative: Provides funding for one Office Specialist II position and associated costs.
